<section xml:id="Fallacies">
  <title>Fallacies</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>
      The following are common <term> Fallacies</term>.
      They seem like they could be true but they are not.
    </p>
  </introduction>
  <subsection>
    <title>Fallacy of the Converse</title>
    <me>
      \begin{array}{l}
      p\to q \\
      q\\
      \hline
      p
      \end{array}
    </me>
  </subsection>
  <subsection>
    <title>Fallacy of the Inverse</title>
    <me>
      \begin{array}{l}
      p\to q \\
      \sim p\\
      \hline
      \sim q
      \end{array}
    </me>
    <p>
      The reason these are fallacies are covered in the previous write-up.
    </p>
  </subsection>
</section>